==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Probity
<hw>Prob"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>probit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. L. <ets>probitas</ets>, fr.
<ets>probus</ets> good, proper, honest. Cf. <er>Prove</er>.]</ety>
<def>Tried virtue or integrity; approved moral excellence; honesty;
rectitude; uprightness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Probity</xex> of mind.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Probity</er>, <er>Integrity</er>.</syn>
<usage> <xex>Probity</xex> denotes unimpeachable honesty and virtue,
shown especially by the performance of those obligations, called
<xex>imperfect</xex>, which the laws of the state do not reach, and can
not enforce. <xex>Integrity</xex> denotes a <xex>whole</xex>-hearted
honesty, and especially that which excludes all injustice that might
favor one's self. It has a peculiar reference to uprightness in mutual
dealings, transfer of property, and the execution of trusts for
others.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Problem</ent>⟦br⟧
